-- W7/W9: an out-of-bounds Array index.  Since #16b the bound check lives in the
-- prelude's `impl Index (Array a) Int a`, which raises the coded `indexError`
-- (E-INDEX-OOB) — so this needs the real prelude (MODULES corpus).  Both the native
-- oracle and the WasmGC module abort with EMPTY stdout (native: stderr + nonzero
-- exit; WasmGC: a trap).  The gate compares stdout, so empty == empty.
main = [|5, 6, 7|].[9]
